<title>USA: Netscape CEO asks execs to open Intranets.</title>
<headline>Netscape CEO asks execs to open Intranets.</headline>
<byline>Bob Tourtellotte</byline>
<dateline>ANAHEIM, Calif. 1996-09-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Jim Barksdale, Netscape Communications Corp's hard-driving chief executive, made a strong plea to executives Tuesday to open their corporate intranets to outsiders.</p>
<p>After unveiling a new set of software tools on Monday under the name &quot;AppFoundry&quot;, Barksdale told executives the software can cut costs and improve customer service.</p>
<p>The challenge is to &quot;build internal applications that can run inside a firewall and outside a firewall,&quot; Barksdale told audience members at the First Internet Commerce Expo, here.</p>
